1
00:01:50,020 --> 00:01:56,100
=Later, I Laughed=

2
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:06,600
(Studies show that)

3
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,980
(the heart is an organ of emotion.)

4
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:10,570
(Emotional stimulation induces)

5
00:02:10,570 --> 00:02:13,510
(the body
to release adrenaline and cortisol.)

6
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,640
(These hormones)

7
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:17,470
(stimulate the respiratory
and cardiovascular centers,)

8
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,980
(causing an increase
in respiration and heart rate.)

9
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:21,090
(We can anticipate)

10
00:02:21,090 --> 00:02:23,190
(mood swings by monitoring changes)

11
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,260
(in a person's heart rate.)

12
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:28,380
(If a heart beats
more than 100 times per minute,)

13
00:02:28,390 --> 00:02:29,480
(it is tachycardia.)

14
00:02:32,130 --> 00:02:34,440
(Tachycardia can be caused)

15
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,760
(by anger, fear,)

16
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,390
(stress, anxiety,)

17
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,580
(excitement,)

18
00:02:44,010 --> 00:02:46,070
(or falling in love with someone.)

19
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:05,950
Who are you?

20
00:03:06,670 --> 00:03:07,950
That's my girlfriend.

21
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:14,470
I don't know who you're talking about.

22
00:03:15,290 --> 00:03:16,470
But I don't date girls

23
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:18,670
who have boyfriends.

24
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,390
When we were together,

25
00:03:22,090 --> 00:03:23,670
you must have already broken up.

26
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:35,040
(Zheng Hao's heart rate at this moment)

27
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,260
(has reached 180.)

28
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,020
(This is abnormal.)

29
00:03:38,290 --> 00:03:40,390
(He should seek medical help
as soon as possible.)

30
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:45,820
=Episode 7=

31
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,010
Yong,
this watch measures your heart rate?

32
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:53,670
Yes, it's the latest technology.

33
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:56,440
When you get nervous,

34
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:59,950
your heart rate and blood pressure
will go up.

35
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:01,390
Not bad.

36
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,510
Wait.

37
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:05,690
Let me take a look.

38
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,260
What's wrong with your face?

39
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,280
Let me see.

40
00:04:10,530 --> 00:04:11,390
It's fine.

41
00:04:11,570 --> 00:04:13,670
I met one of
my ex-girlfriends' ex-boyfriends.

42
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:15,410
It worked.

43
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:16,840
Yes, it works well.

44
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:19,110
Aren't you curious who beat up Shi Ye?

45
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:20,400
Why should we?

46
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:21,570
He just told us.

47
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:22,730
He has many ex-girlfriends.

48
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:24,520
Ex-girlfriends have more ex-boyfriends.

49
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,960
This is bound to happen.

50
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,500
I used to be like him.

51
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:31,250
You can see the heart rate data

52
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,010
- on your phone?
- Here's a chance for me.

53
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:35,400
- Yes.
- When I'm nervous, my heart rate goes up.

54
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,400
When one gets nervous,
the heart rate goes up.

55
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,660
You can tell it from the watch.

56
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:39,410
Yes.

57
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,640
If there's a beauty in front of you,

58
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:43,540
will your heart rate go up?

59
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:47,010
No way. I'm too old for that.

60
00:04:47,010 --> 00:04:48,740
Besides, I have my wife.

61
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:53,680
Give it to me.

62
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,500
Give me your hand.

63
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,360
Look at me.

64
00:05:05,410 --> 00:05:06,250
Dong.

65
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:08,010
Check Shi Ye's heart rate for me.

66
00:05:08,010 --> 00:05:09,320
Wait a minute.

67
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,160
60.

68
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,380
Now it's 55.

69
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:13,420
Rather than increasing,
his heart rate went down.

70
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:15,420
I'm going on stage now.

71
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,170
- Have fun.
- Come on.

72
00:05:17,170 --> 00:05:18,010
Go.

73
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:18,890
Go for it.

74
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,780
Good luck.

75
00:05:20,610 --> 00:05:22,060
Hello, I'm Shi Ye.

76
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,560
His heart rate doesn't change.

77
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:31,710
When will I have a strong heart
like he does?

78
00:05:33,050 --> 00:05:35,110
When can I get rid of awkward silence?

79
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:41,100
(Zhonghe Group)

80
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,120
Okay.

81
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,060
That's it for today's meeting.

82
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:48,110
I have another announcement.

83
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:49,440
Considering work arrangements

84
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,520
and personal wishes,

85
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:52,840
Wu Xiuya from Team 1 will work

86
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:55,110
under the command of
Team 2 leader Ma Chao.

87
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,240
Dismissed.

88
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,060
Are you crazy?

89
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:05,230
You dug your own grave.

90
00:06:07,130 --> 00:06:07,980
Wait.

91
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,400
You're not here to get back
at Ma Chao, are you?

92
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,300
Of course not.

93
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,760
I'm here because Wang Tong has left.

94
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,640
There are only the three of you left.

95
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,760
Ma Chao and Zou don't work.

96
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,060
You would be so exhausted.

97
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,760
Thank you very much.

98
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,060
You're too kind.

99
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,500
Actually, that's not the case.

100
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:25,720
I think our team has a shot

101
00:06:25,730 --> 00:06:28,400
at doing the tea drinks promotion
in practice.

102
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,520
I don't want to let Ma Chao

103
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,860
steal my credit.

104
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:33,320
Do you really think Pang Jing
was complimenting you?

105
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,180
In the workplace,

106
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:36,500
kindness stands for naivety.

107
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,300
Watch your back.

108
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:40,640
Ma Chao will do his best
to stab you in the back.

109
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,500
It's fine. I'm prepared for that.

110
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,940
I've seen what Ma Chao is capable of.

111
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,400
Then you've underestimated him.

112
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,320
Ever since he became a leader,

113
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,500
he's been
pushing the boundaries of stupidity.

114
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:53,800
Listen.

115
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:55,640
Even Pang Jing is swearing.

116
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,520
I'd like to see

117
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,620
what tricks he has up his sleeve.

118
00:07:57,300 --> 00:08:00,260
(Nine Tricks to Victorious Leadership)

119
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:15,480
Go on.

120
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,080
I'm not done yet.

121
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,940
I know.

122
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,740
Can't I take a look?

123
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,830
Is that all you're going to change?

124
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:30,980
That's not good enough.

125
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,360
Here.

126
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,860
Here and here.

127
00:08:33,970 --> 00:08:35,090
They all need modification.

128
00:08:35,090 --> 00:08:36,430
But I've already modified these

129
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,740
at Manager Hu's request.

130
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,430
I know.

131
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:45,210
I'm not saying
Manager Hu's proposal isn't good.

132
00:08:45,210 --> 00:08:47,660
I'm saying that your PPT itself

133
00:08:47,970 --> 00:08:48,810
is not good enough.

134
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,310
Then tell me about it.

135
00:08:55,970 --> 00:08:58,330
First, there's something off
with your layout.

136
00:08:58,330 --> 00:08:59,730
It doesn't look clear enough.

137
00:08:59,730 --> 00:09:01,520
And the color is too bright.

138
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:02,500
It doesn't look classy.

139
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,450
The fonts are not uniform.

140
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:05,400
It makes people dizzy.

141
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,950
Redo the PPT.

142
00:09:08,330 --> 00:09:09,310
I'll take a look then.

143
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:23,340
(2016 First Quarter Publicity Plan,
Second Draft)

144
00:09:25,330 --> 00:09:26,430
This one's even worse.

145
00:09:26,850 --> 00:09:28,520
The font sizes are uniform.

146
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,620
There's no emphasis.

147
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:31,980
You said you wanted uniform fonts.

148
00:09:32,210 --> 00:09:33,070
Not possible.

149
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,500
I surely never said that.

150
00:09:35,210 --> 00:09:36,190
Redo it.

151
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,940
(Fifth Draft)

152
00:09:44,970 --> 00:09:46,970
You need to use different colors
to differentiate.

153
00:09:46,970 --> 00:09:48,160
The color is so dull.

154
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,330
I thought you said
the color was so bright

155
00:09:50,330 --> 00:09:51,210
that it's not classy.

156
00:09:51,210 --> 00:09:52,760
But it shouldn't look like an obituary.

157
00:09:52,970 --> 00:09:53,860
Redo it.

158
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:00,340
(16th Draft)

159
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:01,860
Redo it.

160
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,780
(25th Draft)

161
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,500
Redo it.

162
00:10:28,820 --> 00:10:32,780
(Drafts with large picture and front,
blue, simplicity, Leader Ma's advice)

163
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,350
Redo it.

164
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:39,140
(30th Draft)

165
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:50,260
I think the first draft is better.

166
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:06,740
(Ma Chao is convinced)

167
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,400
(Wu Xiuya volunteered to
be his subordinate)

168
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,620
(because she wants to take revenge.)

169
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:14,500
(He should prevent Wu Xiuya
from succeeding,)

170
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,740
(but he also needs her to work hard.)

171
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:18,280
(So he came up with)

172
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:19,740
(a creative solution.)

173
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:22,280
(He prevents Wu Xiuya
from doing what she's good at.)

174
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:25,260
Our team needs to change.

175
00:11:25,370 --> 00:11:28,920
This week, our department has
to do three staff interviews.

176
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:31,640
I'll reassign your work now.

177
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,620
Zou Qi, you'll do the interviews.

178
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:37,640
The interviews used to be done by Xiuya.

179
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:40,260
That's what I call a change.

180
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:43,160
Pang Jing, you'll write the article.

181
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,920
Wu Xiuya is in charge of proofreading

182
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,710
and the maintenance
of the official account.

183
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,710
But I don't write as beautifully
as Xiuya does.

184
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,150
I don't know how
to maintain the official account.

185
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,520
Can't you learn?

186
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:56,040
The company is not the market.
It's not a place to bargain.

187
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,380
Your seniors aren't your parents.

188
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:59,260
No one will tolerate your bad behavior.

189
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,620
Quit if you can't.

190
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,620
(Network error.
Unable to display the page.)

191
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:09,110
Xiuya, what's that word?

192
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:11,380
It means that a person is very diligent.

193
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:12,640
But he's also smart.

194
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,260
But he's not stupidly diligent.

195
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,020
How should I deal with this bug?

196
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:18,490
Where's Zou?

197
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:19,590
Where's he?

198
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:22,140
He went to interview at the factory.

199
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:30,980
Do you have further questions?

200
00:12:31,370 --> 00:12:33,110
If you don't, I'll go back to work.

201
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,760
Let me think about it.

202
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:39,920
Then think fast.

203
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,020
I've got a lot of work to do.

204
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:46,500
How's the food here?

205
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:51,560
(Wu Xiuya thought)

206
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:54,590
(awkward silence only exists in shows.)

207
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,800
(But now she finds out)

208
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:58,900
(awkward silence is everywhere.)

209
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:01,880
The head of the MD
of the North and East China

210
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:02,860
are here on business.

211
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,010
I've greeted them all.

212
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:06,370
You'd better get in touch with them

213
00:13:06,370 --> 00:13:09,230
to prepare for future cooperation.

214
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:10,980
Cooperation will be easier
in the future.

215
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:12,860
That's great, Manager.

216
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,200
Communicating directly
with the Marketing Department

217
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,380
will make work easier for us.

218
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:17,880
Ma Chao.

219
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,740
Can you not repeat what I said?

220
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,460
Manager, I'll contact them right away.

221
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,800
I'll visit them this afternoon.

222
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,260
Take Xiuya with you.

223
00:13:28,370 --> 00:13:29,740
Xiuya has other work.

224
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,520
She knows how it works
better than you.

225
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,860
She can help you if any problems arise.

226
00:13:35,010 --> 00:13:35,850
Okay?

227
00:13:36,010 --> 00:13:36,850
Okay.

228
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,000
Right.

229
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:54,760
Hello.

230
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:56,140
- Greetings, sir.
- Hello.

231
00:13:56,370 --> 00:13:59,540
- I'm Li Xiaodong, head of East China's MD.
- Hello.

232
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:01,520
- I'm Duan Rui, head of North China's MD.
- Hello.

233
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,400
This is my assistant, Bei.

234
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,240
Hello.

235
00:14:04,490 --> 00:14:06,380
I'm Ma Chao,
a representative from the CCD.

236
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:07,760
Ma.

237
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,800
- So we...
- Let's talk inside.

238
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:11,040
- Come.
- This way.

239
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:12,020
Here.

240
00:14:14,370 --> 00:14:15,210
Here?

241
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,260
Okay.

242
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:23,610
- Take the seat.
- Please.

243
00:14:23,610 --> 00:14:25,280
After you.

244
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,260
Here.

245
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:27,640
Take a seat.

246
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:28,480
Take this seat.

247
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,040
No need. You're too kind.

248
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:32,160
Take the seat yourself.

249
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,260
No need to be this kind.

250
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,500
That's a good spot.

251
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,720
Li.

252
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,040
Actually, I know many people
from the East China Branch.

253
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:43,880
Really?

254
00:14:44,310 --> 00:14:45,840
- For example, Zhang Jin.
- Zhang Jin?

255
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,490
Is he still at the East China Branch?

256
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:48,960
Yes, he is.

257
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:51,230
He's the Vice Manager
of the Human Resources Department.

258
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,610
He's been promoted.

259
00:14:52,610 --> 00:14:54,500
- Yes.
- I've got to congratulate him.

260
00:14:54,850 --> 00:14:57,040
- We joined the company together.
- Really?

261
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,640
I was his senior in college.

262
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,740
- Were you?
- We're very close.

263
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,470
When in college,

264
00:15:01,470 --> 00:15:03,360
we used to play soccer
and video games together.

265
00:15:03,370 --> 00:15:04,490
Does he still play soccer?

266
00:15:04,490 --> 00:15:07,470
Yeah, we play every weekend.

267
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,140
Can you get backup?

268
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:10,120
Yes.

269
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,000
I'll go.

270
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,820
- You be the backup? Sure.
- How about it?

271
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:13,720
I'll join you.

272
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,380
- We'll join forces.
- We need backup too.

273
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:16,580
- You want backup too.
- Fine.

274
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:17,360
Let's play together.

275
00:15:17,370 --> 00:15:18,850
- Great.
- Do you know Zhou?

276
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,400
The one who likes coffee?

277
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,240
Yes.

278
00:15:21,330 --> 00:15:22,640
Zhou is so funny.

279
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:24,400
He made me laugh so hard once.

280
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,240
What happened?

281
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,490
He was convinced that
he'd got the wrong shipment.

282
00:15:28,490 --> 00:15:31,040
Then he insisted on
boarding the ship to check.

283
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,800
He had to stop the ship

284
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,640
in the middle of the night
on the Suez Canal.

285
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,400
Then he boarded to check the cargo.

286
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,860
After inspection, he found...

287
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:39,990
He found

288
00:15:39,990 --> 00:15:41,040
that the shipment was fine.

289
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,740
- He made a mistake?
- Yes.

290
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,260
He was scolded by the leader.

291
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:49,370
Last time,

292
00:15:49,370 --> 00:15:51,380
he was also in charge of

293
00:15:51,490 --> 00:15:52,760
our shipment to East China.

294
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:55,380
He stopped the truck halfway

295
00:15:55,490 --> 00:15:56,500
for inspection.

296
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,500
Luckily, it was transportation by road.

297
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:01,260
Otherwise, I'd have to take the blame
if any problem arises.

298
00:16:02,210 --> 00:16:04,370
We're not allowed to smoke here, are we?

299
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:06,160
We can't smoke indoors.

300
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,980
Why don't we go out for a smoke?

301
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,280
- Let's go.
- Come. This way.

302
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,120
This way, please.

303
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:12,360
Please.

304
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:14,740
Why are you coming with us?

305
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,020
To inhale second-hand smoke?

306
00:16:16,490 --> 00:16:17,400
Take care of my bag.

307
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,260
We'll be back soon.

308
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:20,010
Mr. Ma, we don't have much time.

309
00:16:20,010 --> 00:16:21,520
- There's much on the agenda.
- Okay.

310
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,380
Hurry up.

311
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:23,640
Coming.

312
00:17:23,620 --> 00:17:30,620
(Mochi Hotel)

313
00:17:39,170 --> 00:17:40,010
Hello.

314
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:41,620
Hello, Mr. Ma, where are you?

315
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,600
They are hungry.

316
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,030
I'm taking them to eat.

317
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:46,650
We won't come back later.

318
00:17:46,650 --> 00:17:48,310
Ask the waiter to
look after their things.

319
00:17:48,310 --> 00:17:50,150
They'll grab it
when they return to the hotel.

320
00:17:50,150 --> 00:17:51,280
Take my bag with you.

321
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,860
Take it to the office before you leave.

322
00:17:52,930 --> 00:17:53,770
Bye.

323
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:58,860
(Wu Xiuya wants to
rush to the restaurant)

324
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:00,460
(and yell at Ma Chao.)

325
00:18:00,650 --> 00:18:03,350
(But she knows that
since she broke up with Zheng Hao,)

326
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,860
(she's at the center of
the spotlight in the company.)

327
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,270
(If she causes trouble again,)

328
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,990
(Manager Hu might really kick her out.)

329
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:18,620
(She has to bear with it)

330
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:20,750
(and vent her anger on the stage.)

331
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,890
Have you ever met a leader

332
00:18:22,890 --> 00:18:24,460
who doesn't do anything on his own?

333
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:25,650
He won't let me do it either.

334
00:18:25,650 --> 00:18:27,650
He's afraid I'll steal his thunder.

335
00:18:27,650 --> 00:18:30,040
We went to discuss a project
with the client.

336
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:31,890
But just when we got to the point,

337
00:18:31,890 --> 00:18:34,140
he took the client out for a smoke.

338
00:18:34,490 --> 00:18:35,520
I now understand

339
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:37,490
what it means to lose someone
in a puff of smoke.

340
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:38,490
Magic.

341
00:18:38,490 --> 00:18:41,750
(The awkward silence
on stage continues.)

342
00:18:42,410 --> 00:18:45,410
If you don't use your phone, donate it.

343
00:18:45,410 --> 00:18:48,040
Why don't you ever reply my messages?

344
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,360
What are you doing?

345
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:50,620
Wu Xiuya.

346
00:18:51,170 --> 00:18:53,620
(The awkward silence in office
also keeps on.)

347
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:04,580
- What happened?
- Catch that rascal.

348
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:05,320
Hurry. Catch him.

349
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:06,710
- Don't let him get away.
- Rascal?

350
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:07,940
Where's the rascal?

351
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:10,750
What's going on?

352
00:19:11,170 --> 00:19:12,860
- Wait.
- What's going on?

353
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,020
- Hold on.
- What's going on?

354
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:15,370
Are you okay? I'll call the police.

355
00:19:15,370 --> 00:19:16,180
I'm fine. I know him.

356
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:17,160
I'm not a rascal.

357
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,810
This often happens
between acquaintances.

358
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:19,650
- Yes.
- Police?

359
00:19:19,650 --> 00:19:20,810
Yes, I called the police.

360
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:22,350
- Police.
- I'm not a rascal.

361
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:24,660
(Xinqi Police Station
Alarm-Receiving Center)

362
00:19:24,660 --> 00:19:25,560
I'm sorry.

363
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:26,650
Next time you scream,

364
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:28,180
look around first.

365
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:29,550
I get it.

366
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:32,180
But I think this incident
is quite interesting.

367
00:19:32,490 --> 00:19:33,760
I can write a story about this.

368
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:36,660
Well...

369
00:19:37,650 --> 00:19:38,490
What?

370
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:42,830
Can I have this story?

371
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,560
No, I'm the one arrested in this story.

372
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,810
I'm the hero in this story.

373
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:47,840
How can I give it to you?

374
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:48,800
But this story happened

375
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:51,140
because I screamed.

376
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:53,800
If this story goes to you,

377
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:55,650
it'll only suffer from awkward silence.

378
00:19:55,650 --> 00:19:56,730
When it grows up,

379
00:19:56,730 --> 00:19:59,070
it'll be embarrassed to
get along with other stories.

380
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,800
But with your financial situation,

381
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,510
you can't take care of this story.

382
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,250
Come on.

383
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:05,970
This is maddening. I'm still here.

384
00:20:05,970 --> 00:20:07,750
You two have even given birth
to a story.

385
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:10,700
I'm hungry. I'm buying breakfast.

386
00:20:10,890 --> 00:20:12,890
While we eat, you can keep talking about

387
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:14,590
custody of this story.

388
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:24,080
You asked me to talk about
what's troubling me.

389
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,120
To better taste my troubles,

390
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:28,060
I'm working under the leadership
of the colleague

391
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:28,830
I hate the most.

392
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,560
My comedy doesn't make people laugh.

393
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,900
My life and my job are becoming a joke.

394
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,830
What do you think a joke is?

395
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:39,180
Yong said earlier

396
00:20:39,450 --> 00:20:41,250
that a joke is made up of two parts,

397
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:42,560
the punchline and the buildup.

398
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:44,490
The buildup sets up
the audience's anticipation.

399
00:20:44,490 --> 00:20:46,660
The punchline breaks
the audience's anticipation.

400
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:49,220
For example?

401
00:20:49,890 --> 00:20:50,730
For example,

402
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,420
my wife ran off with my best buddy.

403
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:55,990
It's been over two years.

404
00:20:56,410 --> 00:20:57,750
I miss my buddy so much.

405
00:20:59,450 --> 00:21:01,080
My wife ran off with my best buddy.

406
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:02,410
This is a buildup.

407
00:21:02,410 --> 00:21:04,490
It makes the audience think that I'm sad

408
00:21:04,490 --> 00:21:06,040
because I miss my wife.

409
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,310
Then I break my audience's expectations.

410
00:21:08,650 --> 00:21:09,650
I'm sad

411
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:11,080
because I miss my buddy.

412
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,220
That's the punchline.

413
00:21:12,730 --> 00:21:13,750
What you just said...

414
00:21:13,970 --> 00:21:15,220
They're parts of the joke.

415
00:21:15,650 --> 00:21:16,900
But my question is,

416
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,830
what do you think a joke really is?

417
00:21:19,650 --> 00:21:21,070
Tell me about it.

418
00:21:21,450 --> 00:21:22,800
I think the essence of a joke

419
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,040
is to look at the world
from a different perspective.

420
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:27,280
The absurdity behind the things

421
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,310
you see as normal

422
00:21:28,490 --> 00:21:29,750
is the essence of the world.

423
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:31,250
When you gave the amazing performance,

424
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:33,310
we saw the ridiculousness

425
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:34,510
and machismo

426
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:35,320
of your boyfriend

427
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:36,310
and your colleagues.

428
00:21:36,650 --> 00:21:37,160
But lately,

429
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:39,040
you've been complaining
about the workplace.

430
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,660
It's like you're pouring out
your misery.

431
00:21:41,010 --> 00:21:42,310
I think that's not a joke.

432
00:21:42,650 --> 00:21:44,080
The harder you try,

433
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,070
the less funny it gets.

434
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:48,590
I used to know how to do this.

435
00:21:49,120 --> 00:21:50,140
Then get it back.

436
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,070
Reclaim it.

437
00:22:00,650 --> 00:22:02,830
I don't know if the proposal will pass.

438
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:05,560
I hope our dad-like clients
can let us pass.

439
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:07,650
It would be nice
if clients were really like fathers.

440
00:22:07,650 --> 00:22:09,750
I've never been nice to my dad.

441
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:11,320
But he has to put up with me.

442
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:13,840
What else can we do? We've got to work.

443
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:14,900
- Fine.
- Keep working.

444
00:22:16,890 --> 00:22:17,800
- Let's go.
- Come on.

445
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,220
Let's take one step at a time.

446
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:26,450
How can we treat our clients

447
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:28,560
like we treat our dad?

448
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:30,600
We didn't treat our dad that well.

449
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,910
We say to them, "You know nothing,

450
00:22:31,910 --> 00:22:33,310
just send me the money."

451
00:22:33,490 --> 00:22:34,930
I think clients are not dads.

452
00:22:34,930 --> 00:22:36,080
They're grandsons.

453
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,490
Only grandsons are so impolite

454
00:22:37,490 --> 00:22:38,830
to their granddads.

455
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:49,650
Only grandsons make

456
00:22:49,650 --> 00:22:51,990
such unreasonable demands
on their granddads.

457
00:22:56,650 --> 00:22:59,140
(Wu Xiuya feels
she's finally getting the hang of it.)

458
00:22:59,450 --> 00:23:00,510
(In her view,)

459
00:23:00,650 --> 00:23:03,070
(people all carry stories with them.)

460
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:04,750
(If you change the perspective,)

461
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:06,270
(you'll see)

462
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,660
(the absurdity behind them.)

463
00:23:08,970 --> 00:23:11,070
This article has only 500 words.

464
00:23:11,210 --> 00:23:13,450
And you made a dozen misspellings.

465
00:23:13,450 --> 00:23:14,800
Don't you proofread?

466
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,030
Five yuan each.

467
00:23:19,930 --> 00:23:20,770
Mr. Ma.

468
00:23:21,410 --> 00:23:22,800
You assigned me this article.

469
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,660
I've written a total of 617 words.

470
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:25,720
How about this?

471
00:23:25,730 --> 00:23:27,450
I'll give you 3,085 yuan.

472
00:23:27,450 --> 00:23:28,900
You can rewrite it for me.

473
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:34,750
Wu Xiuya, what are you laughing at?

474
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,120
Nothing.

475
00:23:36,410 --> 00:23:38,420
I just think Zou Qi is good at math.

476
00:23:47,930 --> 00:23:49,320
I read what you guys wrote.

477
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:50,350
I think it's good.

478
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:51,400
Tomorrow,

479
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,260
after the alignment meeting

480
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:55,040
with Finance
and Retail Departments,

481
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:56,280
if there are no more questions,

482
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:58,520
we can finish the report
by the day after tomorrow.

483
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,270
Then we'll finish on time.

484
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,870
I thought we couldn't get it done.

485
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:06,660
But what's the point of finishing it
for us?

486
00:24:07,170 --> 00:24:09,070
Especially considering

487
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:10,650
the stupid questions Ma Chao will ask

488
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:11,940
at tomorrow's alignment meeting.

489
00:24:12,410 --> 00:24:14,750
We'll be embarrassed
in front of other departments.

490
00:24:15,140 --> 00:24:17,140
We may have to revise the report too.

491
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:19,750
We can stop Ma Chao
from attending the meeting.

492
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:21,140
How is that possible?

493
00:24:23,650 --> 00:24:25,120
Let's change the perspective.

494
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,840
If Ma Chao is not our superior,

495
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,140
but our subordinate,

496
00:24:28,450 --> 00:24:29,800
how can we

497
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:31,510
prevent him from attending the meeting?

498
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:33,510
Tell him not to attend.

499
00:24:33,790 --> 00:24:35,080
Make him work on something else.

500
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,750
Yes, we'll keep him busy.

501
00:24:36,750 --> 00:24:38,780
Make him think
there's something more important

502
00:24:38,780 --> 00:24:39,750
that needs his attention.

503
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:42,160
Today, Ms. Hu gave me an assignment.

504
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:42,920
She asked me

505
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:45,500
to interview General Manager Zhao Ming
from the Finance Department

506
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:47,660
about the reform
of the financial sector.

507
00:24:47,930 --> 00:24:50,220
She said it's an ordinary interview.

508
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:51,560
It's just

509
00:24:51,660 --> 00:24:53,370
that she promised Mr. Zhao
a long time ago.

510
00:24:53,380 --> 00:24:54,980
Mr. Zhao pushed her several times.

511
00:24:54,990 --> 00:24:57,560
So we must publish it
in the newsletter this time.

512
00:24:57,730 --> 00:24:58,830
If Ma Chao believes

513
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:00,320
this interview is very important.

514
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:01,970
Then he'll put his attention to it.

515
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:03,460
Then we'll have room.

516
00:25:03,730 --> 00:25:05,140
That's a good idea.

517
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:07,650
So we're enticing the tiger
to leave the mountain.

518
00:25:07,830 --> 00:25:09,080
What kind of tiger is he?

519
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:10,220
A paper tiger.

520
00:25:10,470 --> 00:25:11,730
Without a tiger in the mountain,

521
00:25:11,730 --> 00:25:13,180
the monkey makes the king.

522
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:19,220
(Nine Tricks to Victorious Leadership)

523
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:30,660
(Zou Qi: Xiuya,
Ma Chao went to the pantry!)

524
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:32,750
Here he comes.

525
00:25:32,750 --> 00:25:34,560
(Zou Qi: Xiuya,
Ma Chao went to the pantry!)

526
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:37,170
I heard
this interview is very important.

527
00:25:37,170 --> 00:25:39,590
Listen, don't tell Ma Chao.

528
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:43,250
I heard that the interview
with General Manager Zhao Ming

529
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:45,030
will go directly to the Chairman.

530
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,410
Financial reform has been

531
00:25:46,410 --> 00:25:48,560
the Chairman's main focus lately.

532
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,800
By then,

533
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,320
when the Chairman sees your name on it,

534
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:52,900
he'll have a better impression of you.

535
00:25:53,150 --> 00:25:55,600
You must do this yourself.

536
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,520
Fine, I'll write it myself.

537
00:25:57,970 --> 00:25:59,320
I won't tell Ma Chao.

538
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:00,210
Or if he asks,

539
00:26:00,210 --> 00:26:02,170
I'll just tell him
like it's not a big deal.

540
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:04,080
He'll attend
the alignment meeting tomorrow.

541
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,660
He doesn't have time for this anyway.

542
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:11,900
Has he left?

543
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:14,700
He's gone.

544
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:37,750
Xiuya.

545
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:39,900
What's your assignment today?

546
00:26:41,890 --> 00:26:43,420
Why are you mumbling?

547
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:45,430
There's an urgent interview.

548
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:47,520
Zhao Ming, General Manager
of the Finance Department,

549
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:48,960
wants a 3000-word exclusive interview

550
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:49,990
in less than two days.

551
00:26:50,170 --> 00:26:51,750
He wants it for this newsletter.

